On Saturday, March 6, 2021 at about 5:15pm, my sister (Lori Best-Andre) treated me out for dinner here. We ordered drinks, appetizers, and a main course. The food and drinks were excellent.  We were eating, drinking, talking, and laughing. At about 7:50pm, the waitress came to our table, while we still had food and drinks on the table to tell us that they needed our table for other guess. We were overwhelmed with her nerve. We hadn't finished our drinks nor food as of yet. We looked around to see other people were there as long as us, and the fact that we had ordered a lot of food and drinks, made it worse. We felt very bad about this, especially when the manager came to our table to say the same thing after we was trying to get our things together to leave that place. I've never in my 67 yrs, have had someone to rush you to leave so they can give your table to another customer. Our tab was $192.03. We felt very insulted and vowed to never go there again. This made us very angry after spending almost $200 there. This was not nice nor acceptable to do to anyone. SAME ON YOU!!🤨🤔🥺
